    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-05-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="564"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10044/187.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-05-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The coronation ceremony passed off very quietly to-day amidst great
                    enthusiasm.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leishman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
